{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-set-up-sending-a-low-stock-notification-for-magento-2-admin/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to set up Sending a Low Stock notification for Magento 2 admin","content":"\n<p>Running a sustainable online store is not easy. The manager must dedicate time to tasks like monitoring inventory levels, arranging shipments, balancing supply and demand, etc. These tasks can sometimes lead to items being out of stock, which is a common challenge for web-based stores of all sizes. If you&#8217;re using Magento 2, you can enable low-stock email notifications to stay on top of inventory levels and avoid stockouts. In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll show you <strong><em>how to enable low stock email notification in Magento 2</em></strong>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To address the common challenge of out-of-stock items, Magento 2 admin can set up sending low stock notifications to ensure timely replenishment of inventory. This feature, also known as <strong><em>Magento 2 low stock notification</em></strong>, allows the admin to receive alerts when the stock of a particular item reaches a specified minimum level. Out-of-stock items can negatively impact customers, causing dissatisfaction and increased shopping cart abandonment. To mitigate this, offering back-in-stock notifications can convert potential customers into actual sales and bring them back to the store. Additionally, to make order status visible on the front end in Magento 2, the <a href=\"/how-to-make-order-status-visible-on-frontend-in-magento-2/\">How to Make Order Status Visible on Frontend in Magento 2</a> article provides guidance on this process. The <strong><em>How to set up sending a low stock notification for Magento 2 admin</em></strong> article also offers information on how to effectively manage your store&#8217;s inventory.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to Set Up Sending a Low Stock Notification for Magento 2 Admin: A Step-by-Step Guide</h1>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Manage low-quantity notifications in the default configuration</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A warning message may be received by a manager when the available stock of a product drops to a critical level. Magento 2 admin allows the trader to set up these alerts in several areas of the admin panel:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Notify for Quantity Below field in the Stores configuration menu under Settings > Configuration > Catalog > Inventory > Product Stock Options sets a default threshold for all items on the site.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1192 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:922px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;576&#x27;%20width=&#x27;922&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 922px) 922px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/59b4df70a1a517b3c4922f51dbbfa2f5/5b5be166f01ce1f3c3506a9b024feb52/How-to-set-up-Sending-a-Low-Stock-notification-for-Magento-2-admin-01.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-set-up-Sending-a-Low-Stock-notification-for-Magento-2-admin-01.png&amp;a=w%3D231%26h%3D144%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T03%3A27%3A09\"