ebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-set-up-Sending-a-Low-Stock-notification-for-Magento-2-admin-03.png&a=w%3D1000%26h%3D879%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-10T03%3A42%3A01 1000w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 1000px) 1000px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":1000,\"height\":879},\"alt\":\"How to set up Sending a Low Stock notification for Magento 2 admin 03\",\"className\":\"wp-image-1195 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"3\"}</script></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Magento&#8217;s Stock Management: Deduction of Global or Overriding Quantity</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Magento subtracts either the global or the overriding quantity from the total available stock to determine the salable quantity.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The REST low-quantity notification endpoints allow merchants to manage their values set in the Notify Quantity fields.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How to get a daily Summary of low Stock by email.</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Create Custom Low Stock Report with Advanced Reports Magento 2</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With <a href=\"https://docs.magento.com/user-guide/v2.3/reports/advanced-reporting.html\">Advanced Reports Magento 2</a>, you can create a custom report specifically for tracking low stock levels. Check out the demo store for an example of this type of report.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once created, you can schedule automatic report submissions to be sent directly to your email. This provides you with regular, accurate updates on your store&#8217;s inventory balances.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Planning your inventory supply</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Maximize Profits with Inventory Planning in Magento: Use the Inventory Planner Module</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Proper inventory supply planning is crucial for maximizing profits and efficiently utilizing warehouse space. However, inventory planning in Magento is not a built-in feature and requires the use of spreadsheets or external platforms, which can be time-consuming to set up and manage. To address this challenge, Magento 2 admin can set up sending a low stock notification to receive alerts when inventory levels reach a specified minimum threshold. In addition to this feature, the Inventory Planner module can also be used to automate the inventory forecasting process. With this extension, you will know exactly when and in what quantities to replenish your products, as well as identify any surplus items. In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll show you <strong><em>how to set up sending a low stock notification for Magento 2 admin</em></strong> and how to use the Inventory Planner module to optimize your inventory management.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The module eliminates the need for manual calculation and arrangement and is smart enough to make forecasts on its own. Benefits of using the Inventory Planner module include:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Optimization of stock planning procedures.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Increased confidence in scheduling inventory replenishments.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Easy identification of overstocked items.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4.No setup is required after installation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Working speed is not impacted by the size of the product catalog.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, proper inventory supply planning is essential for maximizing profits and utilizing warehouse space efficiently. With the Inventory Planner module for Magento, store managers can easily and accurately forecast their inventory needs, saving time and effort in manual calculations and arrangements. With its advanced features, the module helps optimize stock planning procedures, increase confidence in inventory replenishments, and identify overstocked items. In addition to these benefits, Magento 2 admin can also set up sending a low stock notification to receive alerts when inventory levels reach a specified minimum threshold. Whether you have a large or small product catalog, the Inventory Planner module provides a smart and efficient solution for your inventory planning needs. In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll show you <strong><em>how to set up sending a low stock notification for Magento 2 admin</em></strong> and how to use the Inventory Planner module to optimize your inventory management.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-set-up-sending-a-low-stock-notification-for-magento-2-admin/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopin='true' alt='fb-share-icon' title='Facebook Share' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/fb_icons/en_US.svg' /></a></div><div class='sf_twiter sf_icon' style='display: inline-block;vertical-align: middle;width: auto;margin-left: 7px;'>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<a target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?text=How+to+set+up+Sending+a+Low+Stock+notification+for+Magento+2+admin+https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fhow-to-set-up-sending-a-low-stock-notification-for-magento-2-admin%2F'style='display:inline-block' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img data-pin-nopin= true class='sfsi_wicon' src='https://webguru.dev/wp-content/plugins/ultimate-social-media-icons/images/share_icons/Twitter_Tweet/en_US_Tweet.svg' alt='Tweet' title='Tweet' >\r\n\t\t\t\t\t\t</a>\r\n\t\t\t\t\t</div></div></div><div class=\"saboxplugin-wrap\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Person\" itemscope itemprop=\"author\"><div class=\"saboxplugin-tab\"><div class=\"saboxplugin-gravatar\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"